        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-70">
                    <div class="path-to-cert-content view-more-view-less">
                        <div class="path-to-cert-content-summary">
                            <h2 class="section-heading"> Steps to get CISM Certification Online </h2>
                            <p style="display:inline;">Becoming a Certified Information Security Manager is quite simple with our immersive, hands-on training. You are just a few steps away from strengthening your knowledge on IT security systems. Clear the CISM exam and validate your knowledge on assessing and managing online security risks. Here are the steps to get certified:</p><span class="view-more-link">.....</span> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-more-link">View more</a>
                            <div class="view-more-data editor-content" id="path-to-cert-data" style="display:none;">
                                <p><b>1. Get Trained&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>First off, you need to check if you meet the eligibility criteria for the <b>Certified Information Security Manager training</b>. You need at least five years of professional information security management work experience to apply for the certification. You must obtain it within the ten-year period preceding the application date. Once done, you must then train yourself in all the four CISM domain areas. An effective way of doing so is by signing up for the CISM training offered by KnowledgeHut. Check out the available schedules and choose one that best suits you.&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>2. Take the Exam&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>This is the obvious next step after completing the Certified Information Security Manager training. You will have to register for the exam on the ISACA website. ISACA is the certification body. Once you’ve successfully passed the examination, you will be notified of your score, and you’ll also receive all the information you need to apply for the CISM certification.&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>3. Get Certified&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Once you pass the CISM exam, you can now apply for the certification on the ISACA website. All candidates must apply for the certification within 5 years of passing the exam, as per instructions laid down by ISACA. You must also show that you have at least five years’ experience in professional information security management. You need to pay a $50 application processing fee and submit your application. &nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div> <a id="" href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-less-link hide">View Less</a>
