    <section class="course-cert-faq" id="faq-1">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <h2 class="section-heading">CISM Certification Course FAQs</h2>
            <div class="course-cert-faq-summary">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-8 col-md-8 col-sm-70">
                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="cism-course-1">
                            <h3>CISM Course</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="faq-accordion-1">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-1">1. How does a CISM® certification help me?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM certification helps you transition into senior roles in information security. In order to apply for the CISM® certification, you must already have a minimum of 5 years’ experience as a professional information security manager. The certification will:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Validate your expertise across all four information security domains &nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Prepare you for senior roles in information security &nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Enable you to build a robust information security governance framework for your organization&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Understand latest practices in information security &nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Command higher salaries than your non-certified peers &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-2">2. Is this CISM course only for security professionals?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Not necessarily. While the CISM training requires a minimum of five years of experience in professional information security management (across the four domains), it is open to the following individuals:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Professionals preparing to become CISM certified&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>CISA or CISSP-certified individuals looking to move into information security management&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>General security management professionals looking to move into information security&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Information security managers&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-3">3. What are the prerequisites to attend the CISM® course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>You must have minimum 5 years’ work experience in professional information security management.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Your work experience must be spread across the four domains of information security and verified by your employer(s).&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-4">4. What next after CISM® Certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Once you have gained the CISM® Certification, you can consider pursuing the following courses: &nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>CGEIT—Certified in the Governance of Enterprise IT&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>CSX-P—Cybersecurity Practitioner Certification&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-5">5. Do I need to renew my CISM® Certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM credential is valid for three years. CISMs must comply with the following requirements to retain certification:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Earn and report a minimum of one hundred and twenty (120) CPE hours for a three-year reporting cycle period.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Pay the CISM annual maintenance fee ($45 for members, $85 for non-members)&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Comply with the <a href="https://www.isaca.org/credentialing/annual-cpe-audit" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">annual CPE audit</a> if selected&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Comply with <a href="https://www.isaca.org/credentialing/code-of-professional-ethics" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">ISACA’s Code of Professional Ethics</a> &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>Failure to comply with these certification requirements will result in the revocation of an individual’s CISM designation.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-6">6. What does CISM stand for?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>CISM stands for ‘Certified Information Security Manager’<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-7">7. What is CISM certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM certification refers to the Certified Information Security Manager credential given by ISACA. It’s usually given to professionals with experience in IT and information security who are looking to accelerate their career by moving into managerial roles.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-8">8. What is CISM course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-8" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The <b>CISM course</b> or Certified Information Security Manager course helps all Information Security professionals gain the skills required to move into managerial roles in information security and control. This course is awarded by the Information Systems Audit and Control Association (ISACA).<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-9">9. Why is CISM important?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-9" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM certification helps you transition into senior roles in information security. In order to apply for the CISM certification, you must already have a minimum of 5 years’ experience as a professional information security manager. The certification will:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Validate your expertise across all four information security domains</li>
                                                <li>Prepare you for senior roles in information security</li>
                                                <li>Enable you to build a robust information security governance framework for your organization</li>
                                                <li>Understand latest practices in information security</li>
                                                <li>Command higher salaries than your non-certified peers &nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-10">10. What is CISM certification requirements?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-10" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The following are the prerequisites you need to attend the CISM course:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>You must have minimum 5 years’ work experience in professional information security management.</li>
                                                <li>Your work experience must be spread across the four domains of information security and verified by your employer(s).&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-11">11. How long is CISM course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-11" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM training online offered by KnowledgeHut is spread over 40 hours, led by Information Security experts. The course curriculum is comprehensive in a way that helps you learn all the concepts you need to pass the CISM exam in one go. The CISM classes are conducted by renowned industry experts with years of professional experience.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-12">12. What is the benefit of having a CISM certification training course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-12" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The benefits of pursuing the certified information security manager (CISM) certification training are numerous, but the two primary ones are as follows:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>It shows that you have proven work experience in information security, strategy, and control</li>
                                                <li>It shows that you’re committed to your career as an Information Security Specialist/Manage</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-13">13. Is it worth getting CISM?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-13" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Pursuing a CISM course online is completely worth it. Having the CISM credential boosts your resume and opens the door to excellent managerial roles in Information Security and Control. It also is a clear indicator to recruiters that you have the experience and skills that they’re looking for, in terms of IT security.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-14">14. What is the salary of CISM? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-14" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>According to ZipRecruiter, the average annual salary for CISM holders in the US is $137,058. A <b>CISM training course</b> such as KnowledgeHut’s can help you get the skills to earn just as much, or more!<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-15">15. What jobs can you get with a CISM certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-15" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Taking CISM certification classes enables you to land senior managerial roles in Information Security and Control. Some of the domains you’ll be perfect for include:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Information Security and Control</li>
                                                <li>Cybersecurity</li>
                                                <li>Risk Assessment</li>
                                                <li>Information Security Strategy / Initiatives</li>
                                                <li>Information Systems Development&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-16">16. What is CISM exam?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-16" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM exam is an exam offered by the Information Systems Audit and Control Association (ISACA), as a part of the CISM certification requirements. You need to pass this exam in order to apply for the credential.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-17">17. How much does CISM exam cost?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-17" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM exam cost varies depending on your ISACA membership status, as shown below:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>ISACA Member: US $575</li>
                                                <li>ISACA Nonmember: US $760&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-18">18. Is the CISM exam hard?</a> </div>
