                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-23">23. How to renew CISM Certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-23" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM credential is valid for three years. CISMs must comply with the following requirements to retain certification:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Earn and report a minimum of one hundred and twenty (120) CPE hours for a three-year reporting cycle period.</li>
                                                <li>Pay the CISM annual maintenance fee ($45 for members, $85 for non-members)</li>
                                                <li>Comply with the annual CPE audit if selected</li>
                                                <li>Comply with ISACA’s Code of Professional Ethics</li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>Failure to comply with these certification requirements will result in the revocation of an individual’s CISM designation.</p>
