                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="cism-certification-process-2">
                            <h3>CISM Certification Process</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="faq-accordion-2">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-1">1. Who provides the CISM® certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM® certification is offered by the Information Systems Audit and Control Association®, ISACA.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-2">2. Can I get certified without taking the course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You can self-study and take the examination directly from ISACA without attending a training course. However, it is strongly recommended that you take a training before taking the CISM® exam.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-3">3. Do you provide a course completion certificate?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, you will receive a course completion certificate from KnowledgeHut on successfully completing the course.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-4">4. How to get CISM certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>To become a Certified Information Security Manager, you first need to fulfill certain prerequisites before you can even apply for the CISM® exam. They are as follows:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>You must have minimum 5 years’ work experience in professional information security management.&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Your work experience must be spread across the four domains of information security and verified by your employer(s). </li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p>Then, you must prepare for and pass the CISM® exam. Each candidate’s results are converted to scaled scores using a common scale of 200-800. A scaled score of 450 or higher is required to pass.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
                                            <p>After passing the exam, you must then apply for the CISM certification. Here are the steps involved:&nbsp;</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Adhere to the Code of Professional Ethics&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Adhere to the Continuing Professional Education (CPE) Policy&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Pay a one-time, non-refundable application fee of US$50&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                                <li>Finalize your payment and submit your completed application to ensure an expedited processing time.&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-5">5. Will my certificate say ‘Virtual’ if I take the certification online?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, your certificate will not mention that the course was held online. It will look the same as the in-person certificates.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-6">6. What is the eligibility for CISM certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM certification eligibility includes: </p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>A minimum of 5 years of work experience in information security management.&nbsp; </li>
                                                <li>Relevant work experience spread across the four domains of cyber security.&nbsp;</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-7">7. What is the validity of CISM Certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The CISM certification validity is 3 years. You need to renew it after 3 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
